Triangle $POD$ is a 30-60-90 triangle, so $DO = \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}$ and $PD = \frac{1}{2}$.  Therefore, the coordinates of $P$ are $\left(\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2},-\frac{1}{2}\right)$, so $\tan 330^\circ = \frac{\sin330^\circ}{\cos 330^\circ} = \frac{-1/2}{\sqrt{3}/2} = -\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}} = \boxed{-\frac{\sqrt{3}}{3}}$.

