label("$3$", (3/2,0), S);

dot("$O$", O, N);
dot("$P$", P, NE);
[/asy]

Projecting $P$ onto the $z$-axis, we obtain a right triangle with legs 3 and $r - 1,$ and hypotenuse $r + 1.$  Then by the Pythagorean Theorem,
\[3 + (r - 1)^2 = (r + 1)^2.\]Solving, we find $r=\boxed{\frac{9}{4}}$.

